parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A loose steering column or steering wheel can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering wheel turns freely without turning the road wheels
the steering wheel has excessive play
the steering column has come loose from the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Cracking at Steering Box Mount
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked frame at the steering box mount can cause the steering system to fail, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering system makes unusual noises
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the steering coupling can cause loose steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering system makes unusual noises
the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine oil cooling lines can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: oil weeping from the engine oil cooling lines

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Piston Sleeve Hole
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A hole in the piston sleeve can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: fuel coming out of the exhaust system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Emission system failure can cause environmental pollution, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
The failure of the breather valve can cause transmission fluid to leak onto the hot engine, leading to engine fires, accidents, and potentially injuries or fatalities.

Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to slip or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings. It can also lead to overheating, which can cause further damage to the transmission and other components.
Rear axle failure can cause loss of control, accidents, or strandings, especially on slippery or icy roads.
Unreliable transmission repair services can lead to repeated failures, further damage to the vehicle, and financial losses for the vehicle owner.
The failure of the rubber plug on the side of the proportional valve can cause a partial loss of brakes, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden or intermittent loss of braking power
having to stand on the brakes to slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder/vacuum booster can cause a loss of braking power, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden or intermittent loss of braking power
having to stand on the brakes to slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the ABS system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden or intermittent loss of braking power
having to stand on the brakes to slow down
